  "session:ses_206de32aeffe6N14Ais4ftYRah:prompt": "{\"prompt\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"content\":\"See the email below. This went to my later box. Why did it not get flagged as spam? What can we do to improve the spam filters to catch other stuff that there's zero chance I'm interested in? Even the topic, right? Email list for grocery retail contacts. You understand what business I'm in, right? If not, I mean, that's information we have in our files that I can give you for better filtering. What would help us better filter?\\n\\n\\nFrom: melvinataylor231@gmail.com <melvinataylor231@gmail.com> \\nSent: Friday, May 8, 2026 8:17 AM\\nTo: Dave Witkin <dave.witkin@packagedagile.com>\\nSubject: Verified Email List for Grocery Retail Contacts USA\\n\\n\\tYou don't often get email from melvinataylor231@gmail.com. Learn why this is important \\n\\nHi,\\n\\nWe provide an updated and verified list of Grocery Store Decision-Makers across the USA, including their emails and tele-verified phone numbers.\\n\\nIf you’re exploring expansion or outreach, I can share a sample and pricing details for your review.\\n\\nLet me know if you’re interested.\\n\\nBest regards,\\nMelvina Taylor\\nSenior Marketing Executive\\n\\nIf you prefer not to receive further emails, simply reply with “Remove” in the subject line\\n\",\"start\":0,\"end\":1167}],\"cursor\":430,\"context\":{\"items\":[]}}",
